<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Turn shout/auction off, and quit worrying about what other people are solely instrested in, and you'll enjoy the game alot more<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If only life were that simple.  People, by their very nature, will tend to take the easiest road available.  With the existance of /shout, people WILL shout out things like 'camp check' rather than going somewhere and seeing if it's camped.<br>
<br>
What does this mean?  If someone shouts out &quot;camp check&quot; (or &quot;anyone camping XYZ&quot;) and they don't get a response, they assume that the spot is free.  Then when they walk across the zone and find someone there already, they get pissed off and you end up with spawn sharing arguments.<br>
<br>
So I either have to deal with people getting pissed off because I don't answer their 'camp check' shouts, or I have to turn on /shout (so I hear it) and answer them <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> which disrupts my play</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
To say that role-players on the Firiona Vie server can just ignore non-role-players is short sighted.  This is a multiplayer game.  You interact with other people.  If a significant portion of those people are not roleplaying, it becomes increasingly difficult to continue roleplaying yourself.  Once enough people have given up on roleplaying all together, then Firiona Vie becomes just another blue server (with TLC and 1 character limit). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzarsissrazorscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarsiss Razorscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/10/02 10:26:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=618.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I hate the new changes.</span><hr size=1> I like the arguement that we who play on FV are better people than they who play on other servers. LOL, it was the rules that made us better people.  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=49821">Zarsiss Razorscale</a><br>
